column1: Who will win the 2020 Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Television Movie or Limited Series?
column5: ['Mahershala Ali (True Detective)', 'Russell Crowe (The Loudest Voice)', 'Jared Harris (Chernobyl)', 'Jharrel Jerome (When They See Us)', 'Sam Rockwell (Fosse/Verdon)', 'A tie or other outcome']

column6: Three STRONG contenders here: Ali (great performance of an aging detective with encroaching Alzheimers) in an established series genre; Harris gives a strong and restrained performance in a GREAT dramatic series (which will win the Best TV movie or limited series - drama award) ; and Jerome in When They See Us has gotten excellent reviews, the film has received a lot of critical praise in the press, but not as many people have seen this series.
Crowe's foray into television in a high-profile project should give him an edge. Jared Harris is well-liked among his peers and seems the only strong competition here.
